Female terminalia.
Epiproct (
Figs. 106, 107
) very pale, triangular; apically finely hairy. Each half of tergite 8 (
Figs. 106–108
) convex, its margins straight, rounded apically; upper two-thirds setaceous. Cercus three times as long as wide; with one long apical seta and several preapical setae. Sternite 8 (
Figs. 107, 108
) triangular; with four preapical setae. Spermathecae (
Fig. 109
) simple; length of sclerotized ducts approximately twice the diameter of a spermatheca.
